10 An Act relating to crimes and punishments; amending
21 O.S. 2021, Sections 1902 and 1903, which relate to
11 the Bus Passenger Safety Act; modifying scope of
certain definitions; adding definition; expanding
12 scope of unlawful acts; updating statutory language
and references; and declaring an emergency.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 1902, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 1902. As used in the Bus Passenger Safety Act:
19 1. “Bus” means a vehicle designed to carry passengers that is
20 part of a network of passenger vehicles for use by the public,
21 running on a regular schedule of routes, times, and fares;
22 2. “Bus transportation company” or “company” means any person
23 or governmental entity providing for-hire transport to passengers or
24 cargo by bus rolling stock transit vehicles upon the roads, streets,
