1 high ways, public or dedicated rights-of-way, and turnpikes of this
2 state;
3 3. “Deadly or dangerous weapon” includes all weapons listed in
4 Section 1287 of this title, and any other weapon capable of
5 inflicting serious bodily injury, except for a weapon carried for
6 lawful self-defense in compliance under the Oklahoma Self Defense
7 Self-Defense Act;
8 4. “Passenger” means any person served by the bus
9 transportation company; and
10 5. “Rolling stock transit vehicles” include buses, vans, cars,
11 railcars, locomotives, trolley cars, ferry boats, and vehicles used
12 for transporting the public; and
13 6. “Terminal” means a bus station, stop, platform, or depot or
14 any facility operated or leased by or operated on behalf of a bus
15 transportation company. This term shall include a reasonable area
16 immediately adjacent to any designated stop along the route traveled
17 by any bus rolling stock transit vehicle operated by a bus
18 transportation company and parking lots or parking areas adjacent to
19 a terminal.
